    h2 Checkbox Layout
    p Checkbox layout is pretty simple:
    :code(lang="html")
          <!-- checkbox element -->
          <label class="checkbox">
            <!-- checkbox input -->
            <input type="checkbox">
            <!-- checkbox icon -->
            <i class="icon-checkbox"></i>
          </label>
    h2 Checkbox Group/List
    p To create Checkbox group/list we need to use <a href="list-view.html">List View</a> with few additions:
    :code(lang="html")
          <div class="list">
            <ul>
              <!-- Single checkbox item -->
              <li>
                <label class="item-checkbox item-content">
                  <!-- Checkbox input -->
                  <input type="checkbox"/>
                  <!-- Checkbox icon -->
                  <i class="icon icon-checkbox"></i>
                  <div class="item-inner">
                    <!-- Checkbox Title -->
                    <div class="item-title">Books</div>
                  </div>
                </label>
              </li>
              <!-- Another checkbox item -->
              <li>
                <label class="item-checkbox item-content">
                  <!-- Checked by default -->
                  <input type="checkbox" checked/>
                  <i class="icon icon-checkbox"></i>
                  <div class="item-inner">
                    <div class="item-title">Music</div>
                  </div>
                </label>
              </li>
              ...
            </ul>
          </div>
    .important-note
      ul
        li `item-content` must be a `<label>` element with additional `item-checkbox` class
        li Checkbox input (`<input type="checkbox">`) must be a first child of `item-content`
        li Checkbox icon must be <b>after</b> checkbox input
    h2 Indeterminate State
    p Framework7 comes with visual support for indeterminate checkbox state.
    p In HTML it is not possible to set this state with attribute, it can be set only via JavaScript:
    :code(lang="html")
      <input type="checkbox" id="my-checkbox">
    :code(lang="js")
      var checkboxEl = document.querySelector('#my-checkbox');
      checkboxEl.indeterminate = true;
    p Or with Dom7
    :code(lang="js")
      var $checkboxEl = $('#my-checkbox');
      $checkboxEl.prop('indeterminate', true);
    p But if you use it with <a href="./router-component.html">Router Component</a> then it will automatically detect this attribute and set it as element property, so it can be used in templates:
    :code(lang="html")
      <input type="checkbox" {{#if something}}indeterminate{{/if}} id="my-checkbox" />

